      • parseMol

        public static Chemical parseMol(byte[] bytes,
                                int start,
                                int length)
                         throws IOException
        Parse the given mol record byte array into a single Chemical object.
        Parameters:
        bytes - the byte array containing the mol record
        start - the offset into the array where the mol record starts.
        length - the number of bytes the mol record is long.
        Returns:
        a new Chemical object will never be null but may contain 0 atoms.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the mol record.

      • addAtom

        public Atom addAtom(String symbol,
                    double x,
                    double y,
                    double z)
        Add a new atom to this molecule with the given element symbol and the given coordinates.

        This is the same as : 

         Atom a = addAtom(symbol);
 a.setLocation(x, y, z);
 return a;
        Parameters:
        symbol - the elemental symbol of the atom; can not be null.
        x - the x coordinate.
        y - the y coordinate.
        z - the z coordinate.
        Returns:
        the new Atom that was created.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if symbol is null.

      • removeNonDescriptHydrogens

        public boolean removeNonDescriptHydrogens()
        Remove explicit Hydrogens that don't have any special properties set such as:
        • mass
        • charge
        • atom to atom mapping
        • radical
        • parity
        • In an S-group or connected to an atom in an S-group
        • connected to a query atom
        • has defined stereo bond
        Returns:
        true (currently always even if nothing is removed)

      • setAtomMapToPosition

        public void setAtomMapToPosition()
        Set each atom's atomToAtomMap in this Chemical to it's position in this chemical (offset +1). So the first atom will get an atomToAtomMap of 1 the second atom will get an atomToAtomMap of 2 etc.
